  "commentary": "With SPX at 6603.23 sitting below the 6610 max positive gamma wall in a PIN regime, dealers are actively buying this dip as they're long gamma and providing stabilization. The massive +78.9B gamma wall at 6610 should act as strong resistance with dealers selling any rally attempts, while the -38.9B negative gamma pocket at 6590 creates a dangerous zone where dealer selling would accelerate any breakdown. The recent GEX surge combined with spot trading between the 6590 amplifying level and 6610 stabilizing wall suggests we're in a tight range with 6613 flip strike as the key pivot.\n\nBottom line: expect price to bounce around between 6590-6610 with limited upside past 6610.",
